-- Kuwait Finance House 9-Month Provisions Fell 11% to $435 Million, CEO Says
-- B y   F i o n a   M a c D o n a l d
-- 2010-10-31T08:12:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-31/kuwait-finance-house-9-month-provisions-fell-11-chief-executive-says.html
Kuwait Finance House’s nine-month
provisions declined to 122 million dinars from 137 million
dinars in the year-earlier period, said Mohammed Sulaiman Al-
Omar, the chief executive officer of the country’s largest
Islamic lender.  Kuwait Finance is “optimistic” about full-year results,
he told reporters in the Kuwaiti capital today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fiona MacDonald in Kuwait at 
